852
00:44:08,594 --> 00:44:10,736
which you look for a specific direction,

853
00:44:11,716 --> 00:44:16,400
and they are, I have handwritten notes, it's great.

854
00:44:18,714 --> 00:44:21,355
So certain projects will require you

855
00:44:21,695 --> 00:44:23,016
to view your game from a certain angle.

856
00:44:23,276 --> 00:44:25,856
So this is especially true for 2D art and pixel art,

857
00:44:25,876 --> 00:44:26,717
but sometimes 3D.

858
00:44:27,737 --> 00:44:29,978
And usually you're stuck with the perspective you choose

859
00:44:30,018 --> 00:44:31,218
for the majority of the project.

860
00:44:31,278 --> 00:44:33,399
So you want to reuse your assets as much as possible.

861
00:44:34,179 --> 00:44:35,680
And as such, the perspective you pick

862
00:44:35,760 --> 00:44:37,520
is really important to your character design.

863
00:44:39,381 --> 00:44:41,042
Often these days you make these decisions,

864
00:44:41,122 --> 00:44:43,882
take these decisions for granted, just as how things are.

